parameters.name: maxResults
parameters.description:
integer The maximum number of rows of report data to return. If startIndex is either unset or zero, the API will return as many rows as specified by the value of maxResults. If maxResults is not set the API will return as many rows as possible, up to 50,000.

If startIndex is set to a non-zero value, the sum of startIndex and maxResults cannot be greater than 5000, or an error will be returned: paging past row 5000 is unsupported.
Acceptable values are 0 to 50000 , inclusive.

parameters.name: startIndex
parameters.description:
integer Index of the first row of report data to return. If startIndex is either unset or zero, the API will return as many rows as specified by the value of maxResults. If maxResults is not set the API will return as many rows as possible, up to 50,000.

If startIndex is set to a non-zero value, the sum of startIndex and maxResults cannot be greater than 5000, or an error will be returned: paging past row 5000 is unsupported.
Acceptable values are 0 to 5000 , inclusive.

parameters.description: string Optional currency to use when reporting on monetary metrics. Defaults to the account's currency if not set.

parameters.name: dimension
parameters.description: string The dimensions on which to base the report. Available dimensions are described in Metrics and Dimensions . For more detail on each of the dimensions, check the AdSense Glossary .

parameters.name: filter
parameters.description: string Filters to be applied to the report.

parameters.name: locale
parameters.description: string Optional locale to use for translating report output to a local language. Defaults to "en_US" if not specified.

parameters.name: maxResults
parameters.description: integer The maximum number of rows of report data to return. If startIndex is either unset or zero, the API will return as many rows as specified by the value of maxResults. If maxResults is not set the API will return as many rows as possible, up to 50,000. If startIndex is set to a non-zero value, the sum of startIndex and maxResults cannot be greater than 5000, or an error will be returned: paging past row 5000 is unsupported. Acceptable values are 0 to 50000 , inclusive.

parameters.name: metric
parameters.description: string The numeric columns to include in the report. Available metrics are described in Metrics and Dimensions . For more information on each of the metrics, check the AdSense Glossary .

parameters.name: sort
parameters.description: string The name of a dimension or metric on which to sort the resulting report. Optionally prefixed with "+" to sort ascending or "-" to sort descending. If no prefix is specified, the column is sorted ascending.

parameters.name: startIndex
parameters.description: integer Index of the first row of report data to return. If startIndex is either unset or zero, the API will return as many rows as specified by the value of maxResults. If maxResults is not set the API will return as many rows as possible, up to 50,000. If startIndex is set to a non-zero value, the sum of startIndex and maxResults cannot be greater than 5000, or an error will be returned: paging past row 5000 is unsupported. Acceptable values are 0 to 5000 , inclusive.

parameters.name: useTimezoneReporting
parameters.description: boolean Whether the report should be generated in the AdSense account's local timezone. If false default PST/PDT timezone will be used.
